 Andrew Anagnost - Autodesk Executive











 Andrew Anagnost - Autodesk Executive








Andrew Anagnost
Sr. Vice President, Industry Strategy and Marketing
Autodesk





Resources

Andrew Anagnost on PinterestAndrew Anagnost's Blog




Social Profiles







 
Currently the senior vice president of industry strategy and marketing with Autodesk, Andrew Anagnost has been with the company for more than 15 years. He started at the corporation as an MAI product manager, a role in which he focused on the expansion of third-party applications for mechanical design software and introduced OEM bundles of third-party solutions. Andrew Anagnost next went on to become an industry marketing manager with the company. In this position, he handled the outbound marketing and industry segmentation for mechanical design software and helped launch the Autodesk Inventor. 

Andrew Anagnost went on to hold positions with Autodesk such as director of industry marketing and business development, director of product management, senior director of marketing, senior director of design products, and vice president of both engineering design and simulation products and suites and web services before taking on his current role. Mr. Anagnost is passionate about the role design software can play in making the world a better place and currently focuses on improving cloud business models for Autodesk.








 Andrew Anagnost and Autodesk











 Andrew Anagnost and Autodesk








Andrew Anagnost
Sr. Vice President, Industry Strategy and Marketing
Autodesk





Resources

Andrew Anagnost on Blogger




Social Profiles







 
After earning his master of science in engineering and his PhD in aeronautics/astronautics and computer science from Stanford University in Palo Alto, California, Andrew Anagnost accepted a job as an applications engineer with the Exa Corporation. This Burlington, Massachusetts, computer software company promoted Andrew Anagnost to applications consulting manager in 1994 and to product manager in 1996. Mr. Anagnost left Exa in 1997 to oversee the expansion of third-party mechanical design applications for Autodesk.

Headquartered in San Rafael, California, Autodesk produces a wide range of digital design and engineering software, including AutoCAD, Maya, Revit, Inventor, SketchBook, and Fusion 360. The company currently employs more than 7,000 people worldwide.

Over the course of his 18-year tenure with Autodesk, Andrew Anagnost has served in a series of directorial and vice presidential posts. Since 2012, he has developed marketing strategies and directed general marketing resource allocation as Autodesk’s senior vice president of industry strategy and marketing. In this role he has also led the transformation of the Autodesk business model.






